# Python CV Sidecar (FastAPI on Render)

- FastAPI + uvicorn. Pydantic v2. Ultralytics for local YOLO inference.
- **Anonymization MUST run before any detector.** Enforced by middleware: `/detect` rejects any
  request lacking a fresh anonymization receipt hash (< 60 s) from a prior `/anonymize` call.
- Models loaded ONCE at startup into module-level globals (Panoramax face/plate/sign + gap-fill detectors).
- All image bytes handled in-memory (`BytesIO`). Writing to `/tmp` or disk is FORBIDDEN.
- Endpoints: `POST /anonymize` (multipart) → `image/png` + JSON `{face_count, plate_count, image_sha256}`;
  `POST /detect` (multipart) → JSON detections.
- Primary detector: Roboflow `visual-pollution-pc2as/9` over HTTPS.
- Merged class list is hard-coded: `{pothole, garbage, construction_road, culture_sidewalk,
  broken_signage, faded_signage, graffiti, unkempt_facade}`. Any other upstream class is dropped at the boundary.
- On 3× consecutive Roboflow 429/5xx, fail over to local Ultralytics weights (garbage + pothole).
